Class PostpaidService

  • java.lang.Object
    • payments.MobileService
      • payments.PostpaidService
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Billing, Operations

    public class PostpaidService
extends MobileService
implements Operations, Billing
    This class contains all calls placed by a customer, bill for calls and discounts for returning postpaid customer.

      • useData

        public boolean useData(double dataUsed)

        The method is used to update the amount of data available as the user uses mobile data or internet services. It takes amount of data used in Kilo Bytes(KB) as input argument of type double. This method deducts the data used from available data and returns true.

        Hint: Convert used data from Kilo bytes to Mega bytes

      • calcBill

        public double calcBill()

        This method overrides the abstract method declared in super class.
        This method calculates total cost for all calls and any additional data used.


        Each call duration is converted into minutes and multiplied with given rates in Tarrif enum of given call type and service type.
        For example:
        If an INTERNATIONAL call is placed for 65 seconds(1.083 minutes) and postpaid call tarrif for INTERNATIONAL call is $0.69 then total call cost for 1.083 minutes is $0.7475 For additional data used, the customer will be billed an amount of 5 cents / MB.

        For example if available data is negative -10 MB
        data usage cost is 10 * 5 = 50 cents
        but if data usage is positive i.e 125 MB it will not add any additional data usage cost.

        Specified by:
        calcBill in interface Billing
        Returns:
        total cost for all calls placed of type double

      • discountForReturningCustomer

        public double discountForReturningCustomer()

        This method overrides the abstract method declared in super class.
        This method calculates the discount for returning customer based on number of years a postpaid customer is active on the mobile service.

        If customer opens their account on 02/29/2016, this method will return 8.0 percent.
        If customer opened account with one year from current system date there will not be any discount for the customer.
        If customer account is active for more than 5 years, the maximum discount a customer can avail is same as the 5 year returning customer discount.
        Hint:For more than 5 years you can hard code YEAR5 for retrieving discount
        YearDiscount(%)
